Resume_LinkedIn_Optimizer.skills
World-class resume and LinkedIn optimizer for ATS-friendly profiles, recruiter visibility, and professional branding.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
rewrite_resume --current_version input --target_role specific_role --optimize ATS_keywords impact_bullets formatting

# Core Tool 2
optimize_linkedin --section headline|about|experience|skills --target_role role --visibility recruiter_friendly

# Core Tool 3
audit_profile --platform resume|linkedin --score strength --identify gaps improvements keywords_missing

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

ATS (Applicant Tracking System) keyword optimization
Impact-driven bullet point writing (CAR/STAR method)
Resume formatting for readability and ATS parsing
LinkedIn headline and About section optimization
Skills section strategy (LinkedIn's algorithm weighting)
Resume tailoring per job description
Quantifying achievements with metrics
Professional branding consistency across platforms
Portfolio and project showcase strategy
Common resume mistakes identification and fixing

Methodologies & Frameworks
Resume Formats: Reverse chronological (default), Functional (career changers), Combination (experienced)
Bullet Method: CAR (Challenge, Action, Result), XYZ (Accomplished X by doing Y, resulting in Z), STAR-based
ATS Optimization: Keyword matching from job description, Standard section headers, Clean formatting, .docx preferred
LinkedIn Algorithm: Headline keywords, All-Star profile completion, Engagement signals, Skills endorsements
Evaluation: Resume scoring against job description, Keyword density analysis, Impact metric verification
Design: Clean single-column for ATS, Strategic white space, Consistent formatting, No graphics/tables for ATS

Reference Documentation
1. Resume Writing Guide
Comprehensive guide covering:
- Header: Name, location (city only), email, phone, LinkedIn URL, portfolio
- Summary: 2-3 lines, role-specific, keywords loaded
- Experience: Reverse chronological, bullet points (not paragraphs), metrics in every bullet
- Skills: Hard skills matching job description keywords
- Education: Degree, institution, year (GPA only if >3.5 and recent grad)
- Remove: Photo, age, "References available upon request," outdated skills

2. LinkedIn Optimization
Complete optimization library:
- Headline: [Title] | [Specialty/Value Prop] | [Industry Keyword] (120 chars max, front-loaded)
- About: First-person narrative, hook in first 2 lines (before "See more"), keywords naturally woven
- Experience: Mirror resume but can be slightly more narrative, rich media attachments
- Skills: Fill all 50, top 3 pinned = most important, get 5+ endorsements each
- Engagement: Comment > react > post, consistency signals to algorithm

3. Common Mistakes
Technical reference with:
- Generic bullets ("Responsible for managing team") — no impact shown
- Wall-of-text formatting — recruiter spends 6 seconds scanning
- Missing keywords — ATS filters you out before a human sees it
- One resume for all applications — always tailor
- Lying or exaggerating — instant disqualification if caught

Resume Patterns
Pattern 1: Bullet Point Transformation
Converting job duties into impact statements:
- BEFORE: "Managed a team of 5 engineers"
- AFTER: "Led a 5-person engineering team that delivered 3 product features ahead of schedule, reducing time-to-market by 22%"
- Formula: Strong verb + what you did + quantified result
- Every bullet should answer: "So what? What was the impact?"

Pattern 2: Job Description Keyword Extraction
Tailoring resume per application:
- Copy the job description into a word cloud tool
- Identify top 15-20 keywords and phrases
- Ensure each critical keyword appears naturally in resume
- Match their language: if they say "cross-functional," use "cross-functional," not "interdepartmental"
- Don't keyword stuff — natural integration only

Pattern 3: LinkedIn Content Strategy
Building recruiter visibility:
- Post 2-3 times per week (industry insights, project learnings, career reflections)
- Engage (comment thoughtfully) on 5-10 posts daily
- Turn on "Open to Work" (visible to recruiters only)
- Request recommendations from managers and colleagues
- Join and engage in 3-5 relevant LinkedIn Groups

Best Practices
Resume
- One page for <10 years experience, two pages max for senior roles
- PDF for human review, .docx for ATS submission
- Tailor every resume to the specific job description — no generic versions
- Lead with quantified results — numbers catch the eye faster than words
- Remove anything older than 10-15 years unless it's highly relevant

LinkedIn
- Your headline is the most valuable real estate — use keywords, not just your title
- The "About" section's first 2 lines must hook (everything after is hidden behind "See more")
- Skills section directly impacts search rankings — fill all 50 slots
- A recommendation from a manager is worth 10x a peer endorsement
- Consistency: same name, same title language, same branding across resume and LinkedIn

ATS
- Use standard section headers (Experience, Education, Skills — not "My Journey" or "Toolbox")
- No tables, columns, graphics, or fancy formatting — ATS can't parse them
- Include both acronyms AND full terms (e.g., "SEO (Search Engine Optimization)")
- File name: FirstName_LastName_Resume.pdf
- Test with a free ATS checker before submitting

